Whats driving company specific returns todayRTN and UTX agreed to combine in an allstock merger of equals The combined company will be named Raytheon Technologies Corporation and will exclude Otis and Carrier which are expected to be separated from United Technologies in the first half of 2020 Upon completion of the merger UTX shareowners will own approximately 57 and Raytheon shareholders will own approximately 43 of the combined company on a fully diluted basis

Whats driving general equity marketsStock markets are trading higher on Monday after the US abandoned plans to impose tariffs on Mexican goods A number of MA deals including a merger between United Technologies UTX and Raytheon RTN and Salesforce CRM and Tableau DATA added to the upbeat mood There are several very key releases this week including CPI trade prices retail sales and industrial production
